cs.OS, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.PL 

The paper presents a new OS architecture for datacenter computing, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.OS (Operating Systems) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new abstraction, subOS, which could fall under the cs.AR (Architecture) sub-category. The paper also discusses inter-subOS communication mechanisms, which could be relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents an implementation that supports unmodified Linux binaries, which could be relevant to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category.
